Date: 0/0/1874
Source: Colonial Experiences
Author: BATHGATE
Vol / Page: 97
Edition:
Quote:  Besides such <i>outre </i>expressions, [i.e. malapropisms] there are many words and phrases current peculiar to the mining population. Of these, one of the most inexplicable is the diggers' goodbye, as in place of using that good old Saxon word at parting, they always say `so-long.'
